WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified standards reference for ISO/TS 22028‑5:2026, which
specifies encoding and metadata for High Dynamic Range (HDR) digital
still images.

WHY IT EXISTS
This standard defines mandatory and optional metadata fields, reference
viewing conditions, and colour space encoding for HDR stills. GIOP must
refer to it so that still‑image pipelines (e.g., Hasselblad, Leica,
Fujifilm) produce compliant output.

HOW IT WORKS
The standard mandates:
  - Encoding colour space: Rec.2020 or wider, with PQ or HLG EOTF.
  - Metadata fields: mastering display peak luminance, MaxCLL, MaxFALL,
    ambient viewing condition.
  - Reference viewing: D65 surround, 5 cd/m² background.

WHERE IT IS DEPLOYED
- Still image export from GIOP‑graded timelines
- RAW development for HDR VFX plates
- Archival preservation of digital stills.

WHO USES IT
L2 Engineers implementing still‑image exporters; L3 Colorists producing
HDR stills for print and web.

WHAT PROBLEM IT SOLVES
Ensures GIOP‑produced HDR still images are fully compliant with the
international standard, carrying all required metadata for correct
display on any ISO‑compliant viewer.

